      <h2>Technical Details</h2>
      <p>I love light weight, simple and efficient tools.</p>
      <p>
        I built the pastor app using Flutter. I used Google
        authentication which makes things easier for developer and user. This
        was easy to implement thanks to
        <a href="https://pub.dev/packages/google_sign_in">google_sign_in</a>.
        The first step in the sermon publish process is to select an audio file
        from the device filesystem. This took a bit of time to get right. When
        the pastor presses the upload button the sermon metadata (title, author,
        date etc) is uploaded to Firebase Firestore and the sermon audio file is
        uploaded to Firebase Storage. I also added a screen to allow pastors to
        keep an eye on hosting costs.
      </p>
      <p>
        The public website is built using NodeJS, Express, Pug templates and
        Bootstrap and hosted using Heroku.
